        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <add>ק"ק שארית ישראל</add>
            </p>
            <p rend="align(right)">Congregation Shearith Israel,</p>
            <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>New York</placeName>, <date>9th Shebat 5628</date></p>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <date>2d Feby 1868</date>
            </p>
            <p>At a meeting of the Board of Trustees held this day the following<lb/> resolutions
                were unanimously adopted:</p>
            <p><hi rend="underline">Resolved</hi> — that the Trustees of the Congregation <add>שארית
                    ישראל</add><lb/> learn with sincere regret of the death of the <persName>Reverend<lb/>
                    <hi rend="underline">Isaac Leeser</hi></persName> the much respected
                    <add>חזן</add> of the Congn<lb/>
                <add>בית אל אמת</add> of <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName> — distinguished alike
                for<lb/> his many virtues, his fearless devotion to the House of<lb/>
                <placeName>Israel</placeName> during a long period of usefulness, and with an<lb/>
                ability which marked him as the earnest champion of<lb/> orthodox Judaism.</p>
            <p><hi rend="underline">Resolved</hi> — that we tender the Congregation <add>בית אל
                    אמת</add> our warmest<lb/> sympathies for their severe bereavement, and offer
                the<lb/> assurance of our respect and condolence on the melancholy<lb/> occasion.<lb/>
                <hi rend="underline">Resolved </hi>— that the <add>חזן</add> of this Congn, the
                    <persName>Revd I. I. Lyons</persName>, be requested<lb/> to make an Escoba in
                our Holy place of worship on<lb/> then ensuing <add>שבת</add> for the Reverend
                deceased, and also on<lb/> the expiration of the <add>שלשים</add>.</p>
            <p><hi rend="underline">Resolved</hi> — that, as a further mark to respect for the
                deceased, and<lb/> for the congregation he so faithfully and creditably served,</p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>a committee from this Board with the <add>חזן</add> of the<lb/> Congregation be
                requested to attend the <add>לויה</add> at <placeName>Philada</placeName><lb/> and
                to present to the President of the Congregation <add>בית אל אמת</add><lb/> a copy of
                these Resolutions”</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">
                <hi rend="underline">Extract from the minutes</hi>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">
                <persName role="author">Mark<add>?</add> Phillips</persName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(4)">Clerk</p>
            <pb n="3"/>
            <p>Resolutions</p>
            <p>Cong Shearith Israel</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">
                <placeName>NY</placeName>
            </p>
        </body>
